author: NMS_Survival_Guru
body:
Just like any industry there's lots of potential movers in the precision application sector

Agriculture tech it just now hitting the boom stages with more tech becoming affordable so if I were to invest I'd look at solid ag tech companies like Trimble or [Climate field view](https://climate.com/) just as examples 

As far as automation tech like drones or autonomous tractors it's going to be a long wait 10-15 years before it's truly efficient and affordable with lots of different companies so pick one with a solid agriculture background 

Im usually too busy working to keep up on the latest ag tech but definitely mapping and precision application are solid tech that's rapidly expanding and worth looking into as an investment

author: Bananplyte
body:
Okay so first off, /r/wallstreetbets is absolutely the wrong place to come for this.  


Second; it seems to not be all Dr Seuss books, it's the following titles:  
 *And to Think That I Saw It on Mulberry Street*   
 *If I Ran the Zoo*   
 *McElligot’s Pool*   
 *On Beyond Zebra*   
 *Scrambled Eggs Super!*   
 *The Cat’s Quizzer*   


Third; It's ***Dr. Seuss Enterprises*** making this decision for whatever reason, so there's definitely no company you can support to stop this.  


Fourth; I can understand why they would do it to protect Dr Seuss legacy. I definitely - *in no way* \- think Dr Seuss was a racist, but the references and imagery are from a time when certain things were portrayed different from what is acceptable today. Blackface just doesn't cut it nowadays.  


You seem to mean well, but you've definitely come to the wrong place. I don't think there's much anyone can do, it's ***Dr. Seuss Enterprises*** decision to do what they want with their own books.
